    <briefdescription>
<para>A writable reference to a single bit. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>C++ does not offer a built-in mechanism to directly access specific bits in integral types, i.e. <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">std::uint32_t<sp/>x<sp/>=<sp/>0;<sp/>x[5]<sp/>=<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">true</highlight><highlight class="normal">;<sp/></highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> is not possible. The <ref refid="classDali_1_1Accessibility_1_1BitSet" kindref="compound">BitSet</ref> type uses this proxy class to make such operations possible.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1Accessibility_1_1BitSet" kindref="compound">Dali::Accessibility::BitSet</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
